The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 6:15 p.m. Lima time.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  fell 0.6 percent to 23,015.47. The
 MSCI All Peru Capped Index (MXPECAPD)  slid 1.1 percent to 2,890.79.  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian copper
exploration company, slumped 6.3 percent to $1.04 after copper
declined in  New York , said Leoncio Altamirano, a trader at Lima-
based Juan Magot y Asociados SAB.  Panoro Minerals Ltd. (PML)  , a Canadian copper and gold
exploration company, dropped 4.9 percent to 77 cents.  Southern Copper Corp. (PCU\C)  (SCCO PE), Peruâ€™s biggest producer of
the metal, slid 1.9 percent to $31.38.  Rio Alto Mining Ltd. (RIO)   declined 4.1 percent to
$4.41, after gold tumbled to an eight-week low in New York.  Minera IRL Ltd. (MIRL)  , a U.K. gold producer with a mine
in Peru, fell 2.6 percent to $1.11, a six-week low.  To contact the reporter on this story:
